risk elements  the following table presents the amounts of non-performing loans and cardmember receivables that are either non-accrual, past due, or restructured, segregated between u.s. and non-u.s. borrowers. past due loans are loans that are
contractually past due 90 days or more as to principal or interest payments. restructured loans and cardmember receivables are those that meet the definition of troubled debt restructurings as defined in statement of financial accounting
standards no.15 (fas 15), accounting by debtors and creditors for troubled debt restructurings.
