for floating rate debt issuances, the stated interest rates are based on the floating rates in effect at december31, 2008, 2007, and 2006.
(b)
includes term federal funds purchased and overnight federal funds purchased.  short-term borrowings, including commercial paper and federal funds purchased, are defined as any debt with an original maturity of 12 months or less. federal funds purchased represent overnight and term funds as well
as federal home loan bank advances. commercial paper generally is issued in amounts not less than $100,000 and with maturities of 270 days or less. other short-term borrowings include bank overdrafts, bank notes with original maturities of 365 days
or less, and other borrowed funds.
